  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Holistic Resource Management in wetland rehabilitation for women empowerment in Gokwe North district</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will apply the Holistic Resource Management  approach  to wetland rehabilitation in Gokwe as the concept has been applauded for promoting land regeneration. CAFOD has put forward holistic resource management to donors including the Darwin fund but has been asked to evidence success &#x2013; this project would serve as proof of concept and generate evidence for the efficacy of the approach. Benefits accrued from wetland rehabilitation will contribute to empowerment of women in the local communities. The project will target two wards (ward 20 and ward 23) that are located close to Tsungai wetland in Gokwe North district. Tsungai wetland has a piped water scheme that supplies water to more than 5000 people in 10 villages and schools. The project will be implemented by Caritas Gokwe as the Implementing partner.</narrative>
  </description>
